do pet rats get fleas i think my rats have fleas my daughter plays with them all the time and is getting lots of sores on her skin is this an allergic reaction how can i get rid of the fleas heres what you can do if you think your pet rat has fleas you can wash the rats in the sink or bathtub in a gentle puppy or kitten formula flea shampoo scrub the cage in hot water change the bedding and make sure to put flea powder on the carpet around the cage do not put flea powder in the cage and do not leave flea collars lying around where the rats could chew on them do not use any of the topical flea drops like advantage that you would use on a cat or dog a few drops of garlic solution in their water supply will also help discourage fleas also flea bathe all other animals in the house hope this helps Flea Fancy rat Sento Cat Hamster Psoriasis Chinchilla Pet store Dog training Red Hot Chili Peppers Shampoo Dog Ferret Tattoo Domestic rabbit Dog collar Hay fever Ranma __ characters Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Guinea pig Rat Livestock Chicken Pet Socialization Garfield Bubonic plague Lady and the Tramp Internal ballistics RuneScape quests Animal testing Feral cat Kakapo Ren and Stimpy Richard Chase Customs and etiquette of Japan Gerald Durrell Urticaria Beethoven (film) John Frusciante Michael Balzary Electrophysiology Canary Housebreaking Taboo food and drink Professional wrestling match types Eczema Rat Park Collar Social rule Plastic 101 Dalmatians: The Series Typhus Jade Emperor Kitten Boric acid Water Tooth enamel Baylisascaris Black Death Wax play Ron Weasley Minor Discworld characters Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Brown Rat Rabies Equine conformation Chloroform Tobacco Massage Happy Tree Friends Tap (valve) Body piercing Exotic pet Newshounds Magical objects in Harry Potter Carpet Chronic fatigue syndrome Gal__pagos Islands House Mouse Yarrow Labrador Retriever Acne Keeshond Chinese astrology 2000 Australian Grand Prix Krypto the Supe